tafsir[19]{c,v,t}:
  74,19,"So may he be cursed and punished. How did he plan!"
  74,21,"Then he reconsidered and carefully thought about what he should say."
  74,22,"The he frowned and scowled when he did not find anything to challenge the Qur’ān with."
  74,23,"Then he turned away from faith and was too proud to follow the Prophet (peace be upon him)."
  74,29,"It severely burns and alters skins."
  74,30,"There are nineteen angels over it who are its wardens."
  74,32,"The statement is not as claimed by some idolaters that he will suffice his companions against the wardens of Hell and take them out of it. Allah took an oath by the moon."
  74,33,"He took an oath by the night when it departs."
  74,34,"He took an oath by the morning when it lights up."
  74,35,"The fire of Hell is one the great calamities."
  74,36,"In order to strike terror and fear in people."
  74,38,"Every soul will be taken to task for the actions that it did. Either its actions will destroy it or they will release and rescue it from destruction."
  74,41,"About the disbelievers who destroyed themselves by the sins they committed."
  74,42,"They will say to them: What entered you into Hell?"
  74,43,"The disbelievers will answer them saying: We were not of those who discharged the obligatory prayer in the worldly life."
  74,44,"We did not feed the poor from what Allah gave us."
  74,45,"We used to be with the people of falsehood and go wherever they go. We used to speak to the people of misguidance and deviation."
  74,46,"We used to deny the day of recompense."
  74,47,"We persisted in this denial until death came to us and prevented us from repenting."